= Rosario Ibarra de Piedra

*Corriente: los renovadores. Cada consejo suyo fortalece a su corriente — y las otras participan menos.*

A doctor's wife from Monterrey. In April of 1975 the police took her son Jesús, a young militant of the guerrilla, and the state has answered every inquiry since with its flattest instrument: no record. She has crossed the Republic carrying his photograph like a subpoena — anterooms, barracks gates, the President's own receiving line, where she got closer than his security ever admitted. She was not political, she says, until they made her the most political woman in Mexico. She is assembling the other mothers now. They all carry photographs. The photographs are starting to march in rows.

