The state has procedures for every opponent except this one: women with photographs pinned to their chests, standing where the cameras are, asking a question — *¿dónde están?* — that has no safe answer. Clubbing them is a scandal; ignoring them is an admission. For the first time in years, the dirty war has to look at itself in public.

